data.name: label2.Text
data.value: What is Depression? Depression is a common and serious medical illness that negatively affects how you feel, the way you think and how you act. Fortunately, it is also treatable. Depression causes feelings of sadness and/or a loss of interest in activities you once enjoyed.

data.name: label3.Text
data.value: Symtoms of Depression: continuous low mood or sadness ->feeling hopeless and helpless ->having low self-esteem ->feeling tearful ->feeling irritable and intolerant of others ->having no motivation or interest in things

data.name: label4.Text
data.value: Ways to Overcome Depression: -->continuous low mood or sadness -->feeling hopeless and helpless -->having low self-esteem -->feeling tearful -->feeling guilt-ridden -->feeling irritable and intolerant of others -->having no motivation or interest in things
